<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN202-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. pārimakaḷirai iraṅkōvēḷuḻaikkoṇṭuceṉṟa kapilar pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN202">
<l>veṭcik kāṉattu vēṭṭuva rāṭṭak</l>
<l>kaṭci kāṇāk kaṭamā nallēṟu</l>
<l>kaṭaṟumaṇi kiḷarac citaṟupoṉ miḷirak</l>
<l>kaṭiya kataḻu neṭuvaraip paṭappai</l>
<l>veṉṟi nilaiiya viḻupuka ḻoṉṟi</l>
<l>yirupāṟ peyariya vurukeḻu mūtūrk</l>
<l>kōṭipala vaṭukkiya poruṇumak kutaviya</l>
<l>nīṭunilai yaraiyattuk kēṭuṅ kēḷiṉi</l>
<l>nuntai tāya niṟaivuṟa veytiya</l>
<l>voliyaṟ kaṇṇip pulikaṭi māa</l>
<l>ṉumpō laṟivi ṉumaru ḷoruvaṉ</l>
<l>pukaḻnta ceyyuṭ kaḻāat talaiyai</l>
<l>yikaḻntataṉ payaṉē yiyaṟē raṇṇa</l>
<l>levvi tolkuṭip paṭīiyar maṟṟivar</l>
<l>kaivaṇ pāri makaḷi reṉṟaveṉ</l>
<l>ṟēṟṟāp puṉco ṉōṟṟiciṟ peruma</l>
<l>viṭuttaṉeṉ velīiyarniṉ vēlē yaṭukkat</l>
<l>tarumpaṟa malarnta karuṅkāl vēṅkai</l>
<l>māttakaṭ ṭoḷvī tāya tuṟuka</l>
<l>lirumpuli varippuṟaṅ kaṭukkum</l>
<l>peruṅkal vaippi ṉāṭukiḻa vōyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="4">With gardens on the tall mountain, where races fast </l>
<l corresp="2">the good bull of the wild cow that does not see a refuge </l>
<l corresp="1">when hunters chase [it] in the Veṭci forest, </l>
<l corresp="3">so that sapphires shine up in the wilderness, while scattered gold rolls about, </l>
<l corresp="6">the beautiful/fearful ancient town that was named for two parts, </l>
<l corresp="5">being one in excellent praise when victory was permanent, </l>
<l corresp="8">about the loss of long-standing Araiyam now hear </l>
<l corresp="7">that helped you with the wealth they had piled in many crore: </l>
<l corresp="10">o Pulikaṭimāal with a flourishing chaplet </l>
<l corresp="9">who fully attained the heritage of your father, </l>
<l corresp="13ab">[it was] the result of disregarding </l>
<l corresp="12">Kaḻāattalai with [his] verses in praise </l>
<l corresp="11">of one among you with knowledge like your’s, </l>
<l corresp="13cd">  o majesty with an advancing chariot. </l>
<l corresp="16">Bear with my unclear lowly words, o great man, </l>
<l>that said “the daughters of Pāri generous of hand, </l>
<l>may they settle in the ancient clan of Evvi.” (14f.)</l>
<l corresp="17a-c">I leave [them here]/I take leave [of you]. May you spear be victorious, </l>
<l corresp="21">o lord of a land in the region of big rocks, </l>
<l corresp="19">where the thick stones spread over with the bright blossoms with dark outer petals </l>
<l corresp="17d-18">of the black-trunked kino tree that bloomed so that [its] bud ceased on the mountain side </l>
<l corresp="20">resemble the striped backs of large tigers. </l>
</lg>
